{"cursor":"9297","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"{{Infobox clothing type\n| name =\n|image_file=Gold monmouth cap from Inkwell.jpg\n| image_size = 250px caption = Monmouth cap type = Hat material = Wool location\n| = Monmouth, Wales\n}}\n\nThe 'Monmouth cap' was an item of woollen headgear fashionable between the 15th\nand 18th centuries, and associated with the town of Monmouth in south east\nWales. The knitted round caps were used by both soldiers and sailors, and they\nwere widely exported. There is a place called 'Monmouth Cap', named after a\nformer coaching inn, at Llangua on the boundary between Herefordshire and\nMonmouthshire.\n","linknr":234,"url":"Monmouth_cap","recorded":1362566551,"links":19,"instances":["cap","historic","disease"],"pdf":[],"categories":["Caps","History of Monmouthshire","Monmouth, Wales"],"headings":["History","Description","Monmouth Cap Inn","See also","References","External links"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/49/Gold_monmouth_cap_from_Inkwell.jpg/250px-Gold_monmouth_cap_from_Inkwell.jpg","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/49/The_only_known_example_of_an_original_%27Monmouth_Cap%27%2Cdating_from_the_16th_century.jpg/220px-The_only_known_example_of_an_original_%27Monmouth_Cap%27%2Cdating_from_the_16th_century.jpg","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/64/Monmouth_Cap%2C_Llangua_-_geograph.org.uk_-_276714.jpg/220px-Monmouth_Cap%2C_Llangua_-_geograph.org.uk_-_276714.jpg","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/vector/images/search-ltr.png?303-4","//bits.wikimedia.org/images/wikimedia-button.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/poweredby_mediawiki_88x31.png"],"tags":[["monmouthshire","historic"],["plague","disease"],["tam_o'_shanter","cap"],["monmouthshire","historic"]],"members":